eriRouterL2tpMib.name: eriRouterL2tpMib

revisions.description: Updated RBN/rbn/Rbn as ERICSSON-ROUTER/eriRouter/EriRouter to migrate RBN MIB to ERICSSON MIB.
Added new table eriRouterL2tpPeerTunCfgTable. Updated the compliance statements and groups to reflect the change.

Added new objects eriRouterL2tpTCfgRemoteTunnelID and eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunnelContext to eriRouterL2tpTunnelCfgEntry. Added new NOTIFICATION-TYPE eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelStateChange2. Deprecated eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelTrapContext, eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelTrapState, and eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelStateChange. Updated the compliance statements and groups to reflect the changes.

eriRouterL2tpMib.contactinfo: Ericsson AB. Postal: 100 Headquarters Dr San Jose, CA 95134 USA Phone: +1 408 750 5000 Fax: +1 408 750 5599
eriRouterL2tpMib.description: Defines the objects necessary to monitor L2TP configuration information, counters and the state changes of an L2TP tunnel. All mib objects defined in the module are viewed within the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in the v1/v2 or the contextName in v3).

eriRouterL2tpPeerCfgEntry.name: eriRouterL2tpPeerCfgEntry
eriRouterL2tpPeerCfgEntry.description: An L2TP Peer Information entry. An entry in this table corresponds to the resources assigned to a single peer configuration. This configuration will be inherited by all of the tunnels that are assigned to the peer group. Entries are added to the table once communication is established with the peer. Entries are removed if communication is lost.

eriRouterL2tpMibPeerName.name: eriRouterL2tpMibPeerName
eriRouterL2tpMibPeerName.description: This object identifies the name of the Peer on the local system. This peer is the name of an identifier for a tunnel configuration and each tunnel that is assigned to this peer will take on the peer's configuration parameters.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgMedia.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgMedia
eriRouterL2tpPCfgMedia.description: This object identifies the transport media utilized between communicating peers. A media length of 0 means that no transport media type was set.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgVendor.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgVendor
eriRouterL2tpPCfgVendor.description: This object identifies the vendor of L2TP stack running on the remote peer. The length of the string will be zero if no vendor name can be obtained from the peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgRev.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgRev
eriRouterL2tpPCfgRev.description: This object identifies the firmware revision for the L2TP protocol stack running on the remote peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgHostName.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgHostName
eriRouterL2tpPCfgHostName.description: This object identifies the name assigned to this peer on the remote host system. A host name length of 0 means that this information could not be obtained from the remote host.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgRadius.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgRadius
eriRouterL2tpPCfgRadius.description: This object indicates whether or not a RADIUS server has been configured for this peer group. A value of true (1) indicates that there is a RADIUS server and it will be used for authenticating and authorizing access to a tunnel in this group and accounting information will be sent to the radius server. A value of false (2) indicates that there is no RADIUS server and authentication and authorization will be done locally.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgRemIPAddType.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgRemIPAddType
eriRouterL2tpPCfgRemIPAddType.description: This object identifies the address type contained in eriRouterL2tpPCfgRemIPAdd.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgRemIPAdd.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgRemIPAdd
eriRouterL2tpPCfgRemIPAdd.description: This object identifies the remote IP address for this tunnel (utilized only with User Datagram Protocol).

eriRouterL2tpPCfgStatic.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgStatic
eriRouterL2tpPCfgStatic.description: This objects indicates whether the tunnel is static or dynamic. A value of true (1) means that it is static. A value of (2) indicates that it is dynamic.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgLocalIPAddType.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgLocalIPAddType
eriRouterL2tpPCfgLocalIPAddType.description: This object identifies the address type contained in eriRouterL2tpPCfgLocalIPAdd.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgLocalIPAdd.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgLocalIPAdd
eriRouterL2tpPCfgLocalIPAdd.description: This object indicates the local IP address for this tunnel (utilized only with UDP).

eriRouterL2tpPCfgMode.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgMode
eriRouterL2tpPCfgMode.description: This object indicates whether the peer is operating as an LNS, a LAC, or both.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgMaxTunnels.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgMaxTunnels
eriRouterL2tpPCfgMaxTunnels.description: This object indicates the maximum number of tunnels that may be configured on this peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgMaxSesPerTun.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgMaxSesPerTun
eriRouterL2tpPCfgMaxSesPerTun.description: This object indicates the maximum number of sessions that may be allocated to one tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgCtlRetranCnt.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgCtlRetranCnt
eriRouterL2tpPCfgCtlRetranCnt.description: This object indicates a count of the number of times that a control packet was retransmitted.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgCtlRetranTO.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgCtlRetranTO
eriRouterL2tpPCfgCtlRetranTO.description: This object indicates the control retransmit timeout in seconds.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessAuth.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessAuth
eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessAuth.description: This object indicates the session authentication type.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgCtlWin.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgCtlWin
eriRouterL2tpPCfgCtlWin.description: This object indicates the control window size.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgDNIS.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgDNIS
eriRouterL2tpPCfgDNIS.description: This object indicates whether the critera used for a tunnel switch is Dialed Number Identification String first (a value of (1)), DNIS only (a value of (2)) or the no preference has been set (a value of (0)).

eriRouterL2tpPCfgPoliceRate.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgPoliceRate
eriRouterL2tpPCfgPoliceRate.description: This object indicates the received aggregate stream limit, in kilobits per second.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgPoliceBurst.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgPoliceBurst
eriRouterL2tpPCfgPoliceBurst.description: This object indicates the packet burst tolerance for tunnels received by this peer group.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgLimitRate.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgLimitRate
eriRouterL2tpPCfgLimitRate.description: This object indicates the limit of the aggregate packet stream transmitted through a tunnel in kilobits per second (kpbs).

eriRouterL2tpPCfgLimitBurst.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgLimitBurst
eriRouterL2tpPCfgLimitBurst.description: This object indicates the the packet burst tolerance limit transmitted on a tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgGroup.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgGroup
eriRouterL2tpPCfgGroup.description: This object indicates the l2tp group which is assigned to this peer. Each peer configuration may be assigned only one tunnel group. A length of 0 means that the group name was not assigned.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgPref.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgPref
eriRouterL2tpPCfgPref.description: This object indicates the RADIUS based preference number (used by tunnel groups only). A lower number indicates a more favorible preference.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgPasswd.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgPasswd
eriRouterL2tpPCfgPasswd.description: This object indicates the password for this account utilized when performing the connection handshake protocol with the remote host. A length of 0 indicates that no password has been assigned.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgHelloTimer.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgHelloTimer
eriRouterL2tpPCfgHelloTimer.description: This object defines the interval (in seconds) in which Hello (or keep-alive) packets are to be sent by local tunnels belonging to this tunnel configuration.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgRecQue.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgRecQue
eriRouterL2tpPCfgRecQue.description: This object indicates whether there is receive queueing of out of sequence messages. A value of true (1) indicates that the messages are queued.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessContext.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessContext
eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessContext.description: This object indicates the name of the session context. A size of 0 indicates that the context could not be determined. Any context name length greater than 80 will be truncated. This will have a value for PPPoE only.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessService.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessService
eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessService.description: The service group to which this session belongs. A length of 0 indicates that no service group was assigned.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgEthEncap.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgEthEncap
eriRouterL2tpPCfgEthEncap.description: This object indicates the ethernet encap type.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgEthSession.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgEthSession
eriRouterL2tpPCfgEthSession.description: This object indicates the ethernet session of which this is a part. This is only set for non PPPoE sessions otherwise it will have a zero length.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgTunnelCount.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgTunnelCount
eriRouterL2tpPCfgTunnelCount.description: This object indicates the number of tunnels that are active for this peer configuration.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgTunCtlErrs.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgTunCtlErrs
eriRouterL2tpPCfgTunCtlErrs.description: This object is a count of the number of tunnel control errors encountered by tunnels connected to this peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessionCount.name: eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessionCount
eriRouterL2tpPCfgSessionCount.description: This object is a count of the number of sessions that are part of this peer.

eriRouterL2tpTunnelCfgEntry.name: eriRouterL2tpTunnelCfgEntry
eriRouterL2tpTunnelCfgEntry.description: An L2TP Tunnel Information entry. An entry in this table corresponds to a single tunnel. Entries are added to this table as tunnels become connected. Entries are removed from the table if the communication with one or both ends of a tunnel is lost.

eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelID.name: eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelID
eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelID.description: This object indicates the ID number of this tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunnelNm.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunnelNm
eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunnelNm.description: This object indicates the local name that was given to this tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgPeerName.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgPeerName
eriRouterL2tpTCfgPeerName.description: This object indicates the remote peer to which this tunnel is connected.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunCtlErrs.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunCtlErrs
eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunCtlErrs.description: This object is a count of the number of tunnel control errors encountered by this tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastCtlErr.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastCtlErr
eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastCtlErr.description: The value of the last control error.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastCErrTime.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastCErrTime
eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastCErrTime.description: The time of the last control error.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunDataErrs.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunDataErrs
eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunDataErrs.description: The number of tunnel data errors.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastDataErr.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastDataErr
eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastDataErr.description: The value of the last tunnel data error.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastDErrTime.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastDErrTime
eriRouterL2tpTCfgLastDErrTime.description: The time of the last tunnel data error.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgSessionCount.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgSessionCount
eriRouterL2tpTCfgSessionCount.description: The number of sessions belonging to this tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgTotActSessions.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgTotActSessions
eriRouterL2tpTCfgTotActSessions.description: This object indicates the total number of sessions that, at some time, reached the established state.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgActSessCnt.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgActSessCnt
eriRouterL2tpTCfgActSessCnt.description: This object indicates the total number of sessions that are presently in the established state.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgTotFailSessions.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgTotFailSessions
eriRouterL2tpTCfgTotFailSessions.description: This object indicates the number of sessions that failed to reach the established state.

eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelState.name: eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelState
eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelState.description: This object is the current state of the tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgRemoteTunnelID.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgRemoteTunnelID
eriRouterL2tpTCfgRemoteTunnelID.description: This object indicates the remote tunnel ID. A value of zero indicates that the remote tunnel ID could not be determined.

eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunnelContext.name: eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunnelContext
eriRouterL2tpTCfgTunnelContext.description: This object identifies the context of this tunnel. The empty context name (zero length) indicates that the context could not be determined. Any context name length greater than 80 will be truncated.

eriRouterL2tpPeerCntEntry.name: eriRouterL2tpPeerCntEntry
eriRouterL2tpPeerCntEntry.description: An L2TP Peer Statistics entry. An entry in this table corresponds to a single peer. The statistics reported are the totals for all tunnels that are a part of this peer group.

eriRouterL2tpPCDataPktSent.name: eriRouterL2tpPCDataPktSent
eriRouterL2tpPCDataPktSent.description: This object is a count of the total number of data packets sent through tunnels that are part of this group to the the L2TP peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCDataPktRx.name: eriRouterL2tpPCDataPktRx
eriRouterL2tpPCDataPktRx.description: This object is a count of the total number of data packets received through tunnels that are part of this group from the the L2TP peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCDataByteSent.name: eriRouterL2tpPCDataByteSent
eriRouterL2tpPCDataByteSent.description: This object is a count of the total number of data bytes sent through tunnels that are part of this group to the the L2TP peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCDataByteRx.name: eriRouterL2tpPCDataByteRx
eriRouterL2tpPCDataByteRx.description: This object is a count of the total number of data bytes received through tunnels that are part of this group from the the L2TP peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCCtlPktSent.name: eriRouterL2tpPCCtlPktSent
eriRouterL2tpPCCtlPktSent.description: This object is a count of the total number of control packets sent through tunnels that are part of this group to the the L2TP peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCCtlPktRx.name: eriRouterL2tpPCCtlPktRx
eriRouterL2tpPCCtlPktRx.description: This object is a count of the total number of control packets received through tunnels that are a part of this group from the L2TP peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCCtlByteSent.name: eriRouterL2tpPCCtlByteSent
eriRouterL2tpPCCtlByteSent.description: This object is a count of the total number of control bytes sent through tunnels that are a part of this group to the the L2TP peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCCtlByteRx.name: eriRouterL2tpPCCtlByteRx
eriRouterL2tpPCCtlByteRx.description: This object is a count of the total number of control bytes received through tunnels that are a part of this group from the L2TP peer.

eriRouterL2tpPCPolicePktDrop.name: eriRouterL2tpPCPolicePktDrop
eriRouterL2tpPCPolicePktDrop.description: This object indicates the total number of packets received from L2TP peers of tunnels that are a part of this group that were dropped.

eriRouterL2tpPCRatePktDrop.name: eriRouterL2tpPCRatePktDrop
eriRouterL2tpPCRatePktDrop.description: This object indicates the total number of packets transmitted to the L2TP peers of tunnels in this group that were dropped.

eriRouterL2tpPCTxSCCRQCnt.name: eriRouterL2tpPCTxSCCRQCnt
eriRouterL2tpPCTxSCCRQCnt.description: This object indicates a count of the SCCRQ transmits for this group.

eriRouterL2tpPCRxSCCRQCnt.name: eriRouterL2tpPCRxSCCRQCnt
eriRouterL2tpPCRxSCCRQCnt.description: This object is a count of the received SCCRQ's for this group.

eriRouterL2tpPCActTunnels.name: eriRouterL2tpPCActTunnels
eriRouterL2tpPCActTunnels.description: This object indicates the number of the active tunnels for this group.

eriRouterL2tpPCTunnelCtlErr.name: eriRouterL2tpPCTunnelCtlErr
eriRouterL2tpPCTunnelCtlErr.description: This object indicates the total number of tunnel control errors for all of the tunnels that are a part of this group.

eriRouterL2tpPCSessionCount.name: eriRouterL2tpPCSessionCount
eriRouterL2tpPCSessionCount.description: This object indicates the total number of sessions for this group.

eriRouterL2tpPCTunnelDataErr.name: eriRouterL2tpPCTunnelDataErr
eriRouterL2tpPCTunnelDataErr.description: This object indicates the total number of tunnel data errors reported by members of this group.

eriRouterL2tpTunnelCntEntry.name: eriRouterL2tpTunnelCntEntry
eriRouterL2tpTunnelCntEntry.description: An L2TP Tunnel Statistics entry. An entry in this table corresponds to a single tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpTCDataPktSent.name: eriRouterL2tpTCDataPktSent
eriRouterL2tpTCDataPktSent.description: This object indicates the number of data packets sent from this platform through this tunnel to its peer.

eriRouterL2tpTCDataPktRcvd.name: eriRouterL2tpTCDataPktRcvd
eriRouterL2tpTCDataPktRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of packets received from the L2TP peer for this tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpTCDataByteSent.name: eriRouterL2tpTCDataByteSent
eriRouterL2tpTCDataByteSent.description: This object indicates the number of data bytes sent from this platform through this tunnel to its peer.

eriRouterL2tpTCDataByteRcvd.name: eriRouterL2tpTCDataByteRcvd
eriRouterL2tpTCDataByteRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of data bytes received from the L2TP peer for this tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlPktSent.name: eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlPktSent
eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlPktSent.description: This object indicates the number of control packets sent from this platform through this tunnel to its L2TP peer.

eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlPktRcvd.name: eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlPktRcvd
eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlPktRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of control packets received from the L2TP peer for this tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlByteSent.name: eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlByteSent
eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlByteSent.description: This object indicates the number of control bytes sent from this platform through this tunnel to its L2TP peer.

eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlByteRcvd.name: eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlByteRcvd
eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlByteRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of control bytes received from the L2TP peer of this tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpTCPolicePktDrop.name: eriRouterL2tpTCPolicePktDrop
eriRouterL2tpTCPolicePktDrop.description: This object indicates the number of packets received from the L2TP peer of this tunnel that were dropped.

eriRouterL2tpTCRatePktDrop.name: eriRouterL2tpTCRatePktDrop
eriRouterL2tpTCRatePktDrop.description: This object indicates the number of packets transmitted from this platform through this tunnel that were dropped.

eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlErr.name: eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlErr
eriRouterL2tpTCCntrlErr.description: This object indicate the number of control errors that were detected.

eriRouterL2tpTCLastCtlErr.name: eriRouterL2tpTCLastCtlErr
eriRouterL2tpTCLastCtlErr.description: This object indicates the last control error for this tunnel that was detected.

eriRouterL2tpTCLastCtlErrTime.name: eriRouterL2tpTCLastCtlErrTime
eriRouterL2tpTCLastCtlErrTime.description: This object indicates the time that the last control error for this tunnel was detected.

eriRouterL2tpTCMaxResendQ.name: eriRouterL2tpTCMaxResendQ
eriRouterL2tpTCMaxResendQ.description: This object indicates the maximum length of the resend queue.

eriRouterL2tpTCMaxUnsentQ.name: eriRouterL2tpTCMaxUnsentQ
eriRouterL2tpTCMaxUnsentQ.description: This object indicates the maximum length of the unsent queue.

eriRouterL2tpTCCurResendQ.name: eriRouterL2tpTCCurResendQ
eriRouterL2tpTCCurResendQ.description: This object indicates the current length of the resend queue.

eriRouterL2tpTCCurUnsentQ.name: eriRouterL2tpTCCurUnsentQ
eriRouterL2tpTCCurUnsentQ.description: This object indicates the current length of the unsent queue.

eriRouterL2tpTCCurWindow.name: eriRouterL2tpTCCurWindow
eriRouterL2tpTCCurWindow.description: This object indicates the current window size.

eriRouterL2tpSessionCntEntry.name: eriRouterL2tpSessionCntEntry
eriRouterL2tpSessionCntEntry.description: An L2TP Session Statistics entry. An entry in this table corresponds to a single session.

eriRouterL2tpMibSessionID.name: eriRouterL2tpMibSessionID
eriRouterL2tpMibSessionID.description: This object identifies the Session ID for a given L2TP session.

eriRouterL2tpSCPktSent.name: eriRouterL2tpSCPktSent
eriRouterL2tpSCPktSent.description: This object indicates the number of packets sent by this platform in this session.

eriRouterL2tpSCPktRcvd.name: eriRouterL2tpSCPktRcvd
eriRouterL2tpSCPktRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of packets received by this platform in this session.

eriRouterL2tpSCByteSent.name: eriRouterL2tpSCByteSent
eriRouterL2tpSCByteSent.description: This object indicates the number of bytes sent by this platform in this session.

eriRouterL2tpSCByteRcvd.name: eriRouterL2tpSCByteRcvd
eriRouterL2tpSCByteRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of bytes received by this platform in this session.

eriRouterL2tpSCMcastPktSent.name: eriRouterL2tpSCMcastPktSent
eriRouterL2tpSCMcastPktSent.description: This object indicates the number of multicast packets sent by this platform in this session.

eriRouterL2tpSCMcastPktRcvd.name: eriRouterL2tpSCMcastPktRcvd
eriRouterL2tpSCMcastPktRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of multicast packets received by this platform in this session.

eriRouterL2tpSCMcastByteSent.name: eriRouterL2tpSCMcastByteSent
eriRouterL2tpSCMcastByteSent.description: This object indicates the number of multicast bytes sent by this platform in this session.

eriRouterL2tpSCMcastByteRcvd.name: eriRouterL2tpSCMcastByteRcvd
eriRouterL2tpSCMcastByteRcvd.description: This object indicates the number of multicast bytes received by this platform in this session.

eriRouterL2tpPeerTunCfgTable.name: eriRouterL2tpPeerTunCfgTable
eriRouterL2tpPeerTunCfgTable.description: This table contains objects which identify L2TP peers and tunnels.

eriRouterL2tpPeerTunCfgEntry.name: eriRouterL2tpPeerTunCfgEntry
eriRouterL2tpPeerTunCfgEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterL2tpPeerTunCfgTable. An entry in this table corresponds to a single tunnel of a L2TP peer. Entries are added to this table as tunnels become connected. Entries are removed from the table if the communication with one or both ends of a tunnel is lost.

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteID.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteID
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteID.description: This object indicates the remote tunnel ID. A value of zero indicates that the remote tunnel ID could not be determined.

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelLocalNm.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelLocalNm
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelLocalNm.description: This object indicates the local name that was given to this tunnel. The length of the string will be zero if no local name assigned to the tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteNm.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteNm
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteNm.description: This object indicates the name that was given to the remote end of this tunnel. The length of the string will be zero if no tunnel name can be obtained from the peer.

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgPeerLocalNm.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgPeerLocalNm
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgPeerLocalNm.description: This object identifies the local peer name. The empty peer name (zero length) indicates that the name could not be determined.

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddrType.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddrType
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddrType.description: This object identifies the address type contained in eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddr.

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddr.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddr
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelRemoteIPAddr.description: This object identifies the remote IP address for this tunnel (utilized only with User Datagram Protocol).

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelState.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelState
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelState.description: This object is the current state of the tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelContext.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelContext
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTunnelContext.description: This object identifies the context of this tunnel. The empty context name (zero length) indicates that the context could not be determined. Any context name length greater than 80 will be truncated.

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgSessionCount.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgSessionCount
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgSessionCount.description: The number of sessions belonging to this tunnel.

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgActSessCnt.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgActSessCnt
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgActSessCnt.description: This object indicates the total number of sessions that are presently in the established state.

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTotActSessions.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTotActSessions
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTotActSessions.description: This object indicates the total number of sessions that, at some time, reached the established state.

eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTotFailSessions.name: eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTotFailSessions
eriRouterL2tpPTCfgTotFailSessions.description: This object indicates the number of sessions that failed to reach the established state.

eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelTrapContext.name: eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelTrapContext
eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelTrapContext.description: This object contains the context name to which this tunnel belongs.

eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelTrapState.name: eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelTrapState
eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelTrapState.description: The tunnel state. A value of 1 (true) indicates that a the tunnel is up (in the ESTABLISHED state). A value of 2 (false) indicates that the tunnel is down (no longer in the ESTABLISHED state).

eriRouterL2tpMibDisableTrap.name: eriRouterL2tpMibDisableTrap
eriRouterL2tpMibDisableTrap.description: This object will provide a mechanism for disabling and enabling tunnel traps. A value of 1 (true) indicates that tunnel traps are disabled. A value of 2 (false) indicates that tunnel traps are enabled.

eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelStateChange.name: eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelStateChange
eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelStateChange.description: A eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelStateChange trap signifies that this particular tunnel has changed state.

eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelStateChange2.name: eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelStateChange2
eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelStateChange2.description: This notification signifies that the SNMP entity has detected that the operational state of a tunnel has entered or moved from the established state. The current tunnel operational state is indicated by the included value of eriRouterL2tpMibTunnelState.

eriRouterL2tpMibCompliance.name: eriRouterL2tpMibCompliance
eriRouterL2tpMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities which implement the L2TP MIB.

eriRouterL2tpMibCompliance2.name: eriRouterL2tpMibCompliance2
eriRouterL2tpMibCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement this MIB.

eriRouterL2tpMibPeerCfgGroup.name: eriRouterL2tpMibPeerCfgGroup
